label chapter6:

    # [Scene: Tidal Flats | Night]

    scene bg ch6_601bcb_1 at full_bg
    # play music "music_placeholder"  # [Music: Tense, pulsing percussion layered with a high, sustained violin]
    # play sound "sfx_placeholder"  # [Sound: Wind tearing, distant pile-driver thudding; a low, anxious murmur from the crowd]
    "You stand at the front of the barricade, ropeline coiled through your palms, the buoy pendant warm and familiar beneath your shirt. Rain slicks your hair to your forehead; salt and diesel sit on your tongue"
    "like a taste that never leaves. Around you, faces are wet and set — neighbors who arrived because hope had, for a time, a shape you could hold."
    show thomas_old_tom_bellamy at left:
        zoom 0.7

    thomas_old_tom_bellamy "Marina—"
    "(his voice cuts through the wind, rough as weathered rope) 'Whatever happens, don't let them pull folks out of their homes. Remember what the flats did to us once.'"
    show marina_reyes at right:
        zoom 0.7

    marina_reyes "I won't."
    "Your voice rides the wind and comes back thin. 'We hold the line.'"
    "Kaori 'Kai' Matsuda arrives at your elbow, neon braid whipping like a signal. Her eyes are a comet—bright and dangerous."
    show kaori_kai_matsuda at center:
        zoom 0.7

    kaori_kai_matsuda "We have them pinned. Keep pressure on the tapes; make it hurt when they try to pass. If they drive in, we clog the treads. Make it costly."

    marina_reyes "We won't get anyone hurt."
    "You say it to yourself as much as to Kai."

    kaori_kai_matsuda "No one's promised safety tonight if you make this a standoff."
    "she snaps. 'But if this delays them long enough, the models shift. People see real living buffers, not plans on paper.'"
    "You feel the town's breath behind you — the children who used to run here at low tide, the shopkeepers with their shutters down, the folks who came because your pulse had given them an answer. The crowd tightens like a muscle."

    menu:
        "Grip the rope and anchor yourself to the line":
            "You lace your fingers through the rope, feel the wet fibers bite into your palms. The cold climbs your arms but your knuckles hold."
        "Move to the front and shout instructions to the crowd":
            "You step forward, rain stinging your face, and shout clear orders. People snap to, forming human barriers where there had been scattered clusters."

    menu:
        "Go back to the flats to pull survivors from the water":
            "You turn and run, rain slapping at your face. The mud tries to hold you, but you push through, hands reaching into the surf for anyone caught in the crosscurrent."
        "Stay and salvage what remains in the Glasshouse":
            "You drop to your knees and begin to ferry crates, your gloves suctioned to wet cardboard. Each jar you can close feels like a small victory amid great loss."
    "THE END"
    # [GAME END]
    return
